		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=1215"><span id=>Kailet</span></a><b><span id=></span></b><br>5 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Kailet&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>Actually, when you reach level 22 or so, your pet is very helpfull.&nbsp;&nbsp;I too, used to think as you do, however, when I was soloing aviak guards in Lake Rathe at level 18 with a pet, I realized that they are more DoT's than anything else.  You summon one up, don't really need to give him a weapon, but it couldn't hurt, then just turn 'em loose.  They cannot tank for you, you have to tank for them.  The 22 pet is pretty good.  They get better as you go higher.  From a soloing point of view, that is.  When I solo, I always have a pet up.  It makes the fight faster which makes for less down-time which equals more exp gained in a shorter amount of time.  <br><br>Pets are well worth it, imho.</p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Kailet Ravenhawke<br>Delharen D'oloth<br>Veeshan</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >2 Replies</td></tr></table><table width="100%"><tr><td class=mhback>&nbsp;</td><td class=mhback >Thread Subject</a></td><td class=mhback>Started by</a></td><td class=mhback>Replies</a></td><td class=mhback>Last Post</a></td><td class=mhback>Rating</a></td></tr><tr class=mdr>
